  "text": "In addition to the climate-based uncertainties are the complex human geographies of food systems, with all their cross-cutting externalities, positive and negative, and feedback loops that extend far beyond the agricultural realm. Intensification of food production methods may have repercussions on consumers' health (Global Environmental Change and Human Health, 2007; [CITATION_1] . Migration of displaced farmers may lead to political disputes. It is in this somewhat unpredictable sociopolitical space that truly integrated adaptation pathways must be developed.",
